This project uses the Flask framework for python.
Refer to the project's documentation for details
on installing it. This is one way but not the only way.
Python's virtualenv tool is required. It's probably
available from your distro's package manager.

================================================
Get dependencies
================================================
Create a virtualenv for the project
$ virtualenv venv

Activate the virtual env
$ . venv/bin/activate

Download and install required packages
(venv)$ pip install Flask
(venv)$ pip install sqlalchemy

================================================
Configure project
================================================
Edit BrewPI/config.py and enter
your own values for DATABASE_URI.
e.g., sqlite:////path/to/file (yes, four slashes)

================================================
Run!
================================================
(venv)$ python runserver.py
